2. It is an inward teaching though by the outward Word;
reaching to the inward ſoule and ſpirit, to the hidden man of
the heart.

3. It is a ſucceſſefull teaching; he ſo teaches as men learn;
he that hath heard and learned of my father; hearing and
learning goe together: hee teaches faith, and wee believe;
humility, and wee are humble; patience, and wee endure,
&c.

Thou art ſaith God to the Church, a ſmall, weak, deſpiſed,
contemned, perſecuted people; but thy ſafety, protection,
bleſſing, lyes in me, and in my power, and wiſedome, and lovs;
